Tukur Muntari, Kano Former Kano State Governor, Ibrahim Shekarau, has described his relationship with his predecessor and successors Governors Rabi’u Kwankwaso and Abdullahi Ganduje as cordial. Shekarau, who is currently the Senator representing Kano Central in the National Assembly on the platform of the All Progressives Congress, spoke at a media briefing in Kano on Sunday. He said, “I and Ganduje have been together for so many years. When I was the Permanent Secretary, Cabinet Office then, he was a commissioner, and we used to interact a lot. “I want to assure you that our relationship has since remained cordial, even up to now. So, there is no problem between us. “The same thing applies to Kwankwaso; we have a good relationship. Our political differences have not, and will not, affect our relationship. I have never defected from one party to another because of him. Copyright PUNCH.
